        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:45PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Midas, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Brief heavy rainfall along with gusty winds that could
knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.
Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Midas and Midas Mine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
